\b\fs24 1. Document Intent\b0\fs22\par
\par
This document describes the Strauss Daly Contract Management System as it is currently implemented in the reviewed codebase. It is written to support infrastructure and cybersecurity reporting and should be read as a current-state application security overview.\par
\par
This document is structured into:\par
\par
\tab\bullet\tab application description\par
\tab\bullet\tab features currently implemented in the system\par
\tab\bullet\tab security controls currently present in the system\par
\tab\bullet\tab current security limitations and risks\par
\tab\bullet\tab recommendations\par
\tab\bullet\tab suggested future security feature implementations\par
\par
\b\fs24 2. Application Description\b0\fs22\par
\par
The Strauss Daly Contract Management System is an internal web-based contract administration platform used to manage contract records and supporting administrative data.\par
\par
The system currently supports:\par
\par
\tab\bullet\tab contract listing, creation, editing, viewing, deletion, import, and export\par
\tab\bullet\tab contract metadata management including:\par
\tab\bullet\tab title\par
\tab\bullet\tab counterparty\par
\tab\bullet\tab department\par
\tab\bullet\tab contract type\par
\tab\bullet\tab category\par
\tab\bullet\tab portfolio\par
\tab\bullet\tab start date\par
\tab\bullet\tab review date\par
\tab\bullet\tab end date\par
\tab\bullet\tab value\par
\tab\bullet\tab tags\par
\tab\bullet\tab description\par
\tab\bullet\tab contract notification configuration including:\par
\tab\bullet\tab configurable alert deadlines\par
\tab\bullet\tab multiple notification emails per contract\par
\tab\bullet\tab multiple notification phone numbers per contract\par
\tab\bullet\tab user management\par
\tab\bullet\tab department management\par
\tab\bullet\tab notification center configuration\par
\tab\bullet\tab notification log viewing\par
\tab\bullet\tab audit log visibility\par
\tab\bullet\tab system settings management\par
\par
