\b\fs24 5. Security Controls Currently Present In The System\b0\fs22\par
\par
This section describes controls that are currently implemented and observable in the reviewed code.\par
\par
\b 5.1 Backend Input Validation\b0\par
\par
Laravel validation is currently used for multiple API endpoints.\par
\par
Observed validation coverage includes:\par
\par
\tab\bullet\tab required field enforcement\par
\tab\bullet\tab type validation\par
\tab\bullet\tab email validation\par
\tab\bullet\tab max length checks\par
\tab\bullet\tab numeric minimums\par
\tab\bullet\tab array validation\par
\tab\bullet\tab allowed enum-style values in some areas\par
\tab\bullet\tab foreign key existence checks such as `department_id`\par
\par
This currently helps protect business-data integrity and reduces malformed input acceptance.\par
\par
\b 5.2 Password Hashing For Backend-Stored Users\b0\par
\par
The Laravel `User` model currently uses Laravel’s password hashing cast.\par
\par
Current effect:\par
\par
\tab\bullet\tab stored passwords are not persisted in plaintext\par
\tab\bullet\tab backend user password storage benefits from Laravel hashing behavior\par
\par
\b 5.3 Sensitive User Field Hiding\b0\par
\par
The following user fields are currently hidden from serialized output:\par
\par
\tab\bullet\tab `password`\par
\tab\bullet\tab `remember_token`\par
\par
This helps reduce accidental disclosure in standard JSON responses.\par
\par
\b 5.4 Application Encryption Capability\b0\par
\par
Laravel application encryption is configured with:\par
\par
\tab\bullet\tab cipher: `AES-256-CBC`\par
\tab\bullet\tab key source: `APP_KEY`\par
\par
This confirms that Laravel’s built-in encryption services are available in the application stack.\par
\par
Important clarification:\par
\par
\tab\bullet\tab this does not mean all contract or user business data is currently encrypted field-by-field\par
\tab\bullet\tab it confirms the framework encryption capability is configured\par
\par
\b 5.5 CORS Restriction\b0\par
\par
The backend CORS configuration is restricted to the configured frontend origin rather than allowing unrestricted origins.\par
\par
Current control:\par
\par
\tab\bullet\tab `allowed_origins` is based on `FRONTEND_URL`\par
\par
This is a positive browser-facing control for same-application integration.\par
\par
\b 5.6 Audit Logging\b0\par
\par
The system currently records audit entries for key administrative actions, including:\par
\par
\tab\bullet\tab contract creation\par
\tab\bullet\tab contract updates\par
\tab\bullet\tab contract deletion\par
\tab\bullet\tab user creation\par
